spans.text: You careful Angels , whom eternal Fate Ordains , on Earth and human Acts

rescued Britain at your Altars bow : And hear her Hymns your happy Care avow : That still her Axes and her Rods support The Judge's Frown , and grace the awful Court : That Law with all her pompous Terror stands , To wrest the Dagger from the Traitor's Hands ; And rigid Justice reads the fatal Word ; Poises the Ballance first , then draws the Sword

Britain Her Safety to your Guidance owns , That She can separate Parricides from Sons ; That , impious Rage disarmed , She
With secret Aid great David's strong Support
Whom They were bid to spare
own Thine , as Britain owns His Hand
make his Fame complete , And fix his Throne secure on their Defeat

Imperial Britain on the Sea looks down , And smiling sees her Rebel Subject frown :
her Cliff the Storm confirms her Power
The Powers that rescued , shall preserve the Throne
Whose Empire they obey , whose Arms they bear
the Nations stand Blessing his Safety , proud of his Command
the Captains dwell On their great Leader's Praise
To be at once a Hero
Hence then , close Ambush and perfidious War , Down to your Native Seats of Night repair
the Victor's Chariot tied In brazen Knots
the Ivory Chair , in happy State He sits
